Body:
Description: Dear team, hello.
We accidentaly locked out ourselfes while changing SSO from IP address of the server to its DNS name. now it is getting an error: There has been an issue with your Single Sign On Process. Please check the Single Sign On Settings.

Unfortunately the failover link was not saved properly. Is there something that can be done from your side to help us with this issue?
Looking forward to your support and help.
Best regards,
Evgeny
What We've Learned Updated: Configured Fail over URL - worked. SSO did not work.
Next Steps Updated: Customer will revisit settings for SSO and get back to us.
